	<element name="Agent" type="Background" source="The Great Houses Campaign" id="ID_NV_TGHC_BACKGROUND_CHAMPION">
		<description>
			<p>You serve the Raven Queen as one of her loyal shadar-kai, immortal servants who stride across the planes to recover memories and souls for their Queen.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Skill Proficiencies:</strong> You can select any two skills to be proficient with</li>
				<li><strong>Tool Proficiencies (Optional):</strong> Thieves' tools and one tool set or musical instrument</li>
				<li><strong>Languages (Optional):</strong> Choose any one (1) starting or exotic language</li>
				<li><strong>Equipment:</strong> A hooded raven-feather cloak, a mask, and a raven skull pendant</li>
			</ul>
			<div element="ID_NV_TGHC_BACKGROUND_FEATURE_GUILD_MEMBER" />
		</description>
		<rules>
			<select type="Proficiency" name="Skill Proficiency (Champion)" supports="Skill" number="2" />
			<select type="Proficiency" name="Tool Proficiency (Champion)" supports="Tool" optional="true"/>
			<select type="Language" name="Language (Champion)" optional="true" />
			<grant type="Background Feature" id="ID_NV_TGHC_BACKGROUND_FEATURE_GUILD_MEMBER" />
			<select name="Personality Trait" type="List">
				<item id="1">I always have a plan for what to do if things go wrong.</item>
				<item id="2">I am always calm, no matter what the situation. I never raise my voice or let my emotions control me.</item>
				<item id="3">The first thing I do in a new place is note the locations of anything valuable--or where such things could be hidden.</item>
				<item id="4">I would rather make a new friend than a new enemy.</item>
				<item id="5">I am incredibly slow to trust. Those who seem fairest often have the most to hide.</item>
				<item id="6">I don't pay attention to the risks in a situation. Never tell me the odds.</item>
				<item id="7">The best way to get me to do something is to tell me I can't do it.</item>
				<item id="8">I blow up at the slightest insult.</item>
			</select>
			<select name="Ideal" type="List">
				<item id="1">I never surrender until my mission is complete, whatever the cost.</item>
				<item id="2">I don't like starting fights, I always think twice before attacking anybody.</item>
				<item id="3">I am honor-bound to serve my Queen, and can appreciate others who follow a similar path.</item>
				<item id="4">I am always ready to kill anyone or anything that gets between me and my mission.</item>
				<item id="5">I will give anyone a second chance, but despise anyone who runs from danger.</item>
				<item id="6">I only take memories from those willing to part with them.</item>
			</select>
			<select name="Bond" type="List">
				<item id="1">I will give my life a hundred times over in service to my Queen.</item>
				<item id="2">Someone I loved died because of a mistake I made. That will never happen again.</item>
				<item id="3">I am guilty of a terrible crime. I hope I can redeem myself for it.</item>
				<item id="4">I lost everything, and now seek to fill that void.</item>
				<item id="5">I'm trying to pay off a centuries-old debt owed to one of my kin.</item>
				<item id="6">I will become the greatest thief who ever lived.</item>
			</select>
			<select name="Flaw" type="List">
				<item id="1">When I see something the Raven Queen wants, I can't think about anything but how to steal it.</item>
				<item id="2">Planestriding has rendered my sense of direction useless. Right, left, it all looks the same to me.</item>
				<item id="3">I turn tail and run when things look bad.</item>
				<item id="4">When faced with a choice between money and friends, I will choose the money.</item>
				<item id="5">I only care about people's feelings insofar as they are valuable to the Raven Queen.</item>
				<item id="6">If treasure is not steeped in memory or emotion, it is useless to me.</item>
			</select>
		</rules>
	</element>
	<element name="Feature: Hand of the Raven Queen" type="Background Feature" source="The Great Houses Campaign" id="ID_NV_TGHC_BACKGROUND_FEATURE_GUILD_MEMBER">
		<description>
			<p>I dutifully serve the Raven Queen. Should I require assistance on my mission, I can attempt to find answers from any ravens present. When I have completed my mission (and only when I have completed my mission), the Raven Queen shall open a portal for me back to the Shadowfell.</p>
		</description>
